From:James Clarke
Get last weeks Barrons and put Grantham's interview on your wall. Then dust off
your copy of The Rediscovered Ben Graham and you will find an essay written
long ago that is Grantham's argument in another era, but like most of Graham's
great work it reads like it was written yesterday. ("Principles don't change.
Thats why they're called principles." WEB) The Grantham interview is
thoughtful, colorful, persuasive, and terrifying. And I hate to tell you, but I
probably agree with the guy that I can easily see the market dropping another
30, 40, 50% from here over the next three years. I'm not messing around with
bad balance sheets, though nothing's safe if the bear case is right. And so far
it has been right on the nose.

We are at the point in the bear where everybody loses money including value
investors, even the best value investors unless they are able to go to cash or
short. Be careful.
